that the concepts of leadership and public morality in the major Asian traditions offer a valuable perspective on humanizing the globalization process. Turning to the classic ideals of the Buddhist, Hindu, Confucian, and Japanese traditions, he investigates the nature of true leadership and its relation to learning, virtue, and education in human governance; the role in society of the public intellectual; and the responsibilities of those in power in creating and maintaining civil society. De Bary recognizes that throughout history ideals have always come up against messy human complications. Still, he finds in the exploration and affirmation of common values a worthy attempt to grapple with persistent human dilemmas across the globe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCivil societyxHistoryxAsia. 0aCivil societyzAsiaxHistory. 0aLeadershipxAspect religieuxxBouddhismexChinaxIndienxJapan. 0aLeadershipxAspect religieuxxConfucianisme. 0aLeadershipxAspect religieuxxHindouisme. 0aLeadershipxHistoirexAsie. 0aLeadershipxHistoryxAsia. 0aLeadershipxReligious aspectsxBuddhism. 0aLeadershipxReligious aspectsxConfucianism. 0aLeadershipxReligious aspectsxHinduism. 0aLeadershipzAsiaxHistory. 0aSociété civilexHistoirexAsie. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z978311044221208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220540uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674030671?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674030671423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674030671/original  a978-3-11-044220-5  Harvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook P